target: ui
validations:
  - name: hud_displays_stats
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the HUD bar at the top of the screen displays the
        player's current money, animal count, visitor count, and game time.
        These values should update in real time as the game progresses.
        The money display should turn red when the balance is low. The HUD
        should remain fixed at the top when the camera pans.
  - name: sidebar_menus_work
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the sidebar panel on the right displays build, animal,
        and research tabs. Clicking each tab should show the relevant list.
        The build tab should list enclosure biomes with costs. The animals
        tab should list species with costs, graying out unaffordable ones.
        Clicking an affordable item should trigger the appropriate action
        (enter build mode or purchase).
  - name: info_panel_shows_details
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that selecting an entity on the map shows its details in the
        info panel at the bottom of the screen. Selecting an enclosure
        should show its biome, condition, capacity, and action buttons.
        Selecting an animal should show its species, happiness, hunger, and
        health. Deselecting (clicking empty space or pressing ESC) should
        hide the info panel.
  - name: ui_click_priority
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that clicking on UI elements does not interact with the map
        underneath. Clicking a sidebar button should trigger only the UI
        action, not place a building or select a tile on the map behind the
        sidebar. UI elements should consume clicks and prevent them from
        reaching the game world.
